Title: Create Your First Computer Game with Stencyl

Description:
With no previous programming or game design experience, build your own amazing 2D games in no time!

Course Highlights
  1. Learn to create games from scratch
  2. Get results from the word go
  3. Actually understand what you are doing and learn to do it yourself
  4. 41+ video lessons!
  5. Over 5 hours of detailed video content!
About the Course

Language of Instruction - English

Course Description

Note - This course is officially endorsed by Stencyl.

No prior experience is required to take this course. Learning from the ground up, you will acquire all the skills necessary to Design and Create your very own computer games, which can then be shared with your friends or even published to commercial markets such as flash portals, the App Store & Google play.

Using the unique logic block system of Stencyl thought in this Stencyl Course, you will be able to create a game of any genre, quickly and effectively. Please follow through the lectures sequentially and always maximize the videos to get the most out of them.

This course contains over 41 detailed video lessons, a game resources pack and many hours of game development training that will leave you confident and capable developing games with Stencyl. Everything you need to know to start developing 2D computer games is covered, including level design, game logic programming basic AI etc. The only prerequisite for this course is that you have basic computer skills, along with enthusiasm and commitment.

This course is brought to you by CyberMyth Games. For the most effective learning experience, it is essential that you pay close attention to each lecture in order and then complete the task yourself. If you struggle, watch the video again until you get the full sense of the lesson.

Get excited, this is a learning experience you'll never forget. Prepare to start making your own games with Stencyl.

Course Content

Section 1 - First Steps - Getting Setup
  1. Welcome to the World of Game Creation
  2. Overview
  3. Structure or Lessons
  4. Installing the Required Software - Stencyl
Section 2 - From Concept to Creation - The Design Process
  1. The Importance of Planning
  2. The Concept
Section 3 - Intro to Stencyl - Starting Our Game
  1. Exploring the Stencyl Environment
  2. User Input & Character Movement
  3. Understanding Attributes (AKA Variables) & Creating the Enemy Actor
  4. Character Rotation - Looking at the Mouse
  5. Making him Shoot (This is fun)
Section 4 - Important Concepts Examined
  1. Events Explained
  2. The Most Important Blocks
  3. Basic Loops
  4. How Stencyl Handles Audio
  5. Creating Conditional Logic - If Statements
  6. The Behaviour Library
Section 5 - Creating Your Own Game Art (Sprites and Sound FX)
  1. Downloading the Free Trial of Photoshop CS6
  2. Introducing Photoshop CS6
  3. Creating the Crosshair
Section 6 - Developing Core Functionality
  1. Basic AI
  2. Camera Follow
  3. Adding the Crosshair
  4. Collision Groups - Setting Them Up
  5. Updating Sprites - A Nicer Projectile
  6. Boundaries
  7. Create Explosion on Die
  8. Handling Avatar States - Switching Animations
  9. Cannot Be Pushed
  10. Advanced AI
  11. AI Bug Fix 1
Section 7 - Finishing the Game
  1. Enemy Shoot
  2. Die After X Seconds
  3. Bug Fix 2
  4. Adding The Helicopter
  5. Creating Health Bars
  6. Destructible Environment 1
  7. Destructible Environment 2
  8. Refactoring the Code
  9. Game Rules
  10. Game Rules 2
Section 8 - Conclusion

About the Instructor

Richard Sneyd Cork, Ireland

Richard Sneyd (B. A Hons.) is founder and CEO of CyberMyth Games. In the performance of his duties within the company, he must wear many hats, including that of a programmer, designer, digital 2D & 3D artist, sound designer, scriptwriter, texture artist, leader, marketer and business man.

He is also a fully registered, qualified and highly experienced lecturer. His speciality subjects include 3D Modelling & Animation, Computer Game Programming, 2D Image Processing, Game Design, Desktop Audio, Psychology, Consumer Behaviour, Human Resources & Business Management.

Richard is enthusiastic about his work and students and colleagues note that he is a very dedicated and accomplished teacher. All of his courses are characterized by a steady, incremental flow of information and a lucid teaching style which is easy to understand and follow for all.

Benefits Accrued to Banks by Finacle

Finacle banking software is based on the best business practices, helps banks enable relationship banking, convenience banking and integrated delivery channel support through Connect 24 that facilitates anywhere banking. The software is functionally rich and flexible and has excellent in built work-flow process with high level security control and audit capabilities.

Finacle software also provides banks with a centralized database and real time online structure and data can be accessed through Leased Line, VSAT, ISDN, Dial-up, etc.

With its high degree of flexibility, the software can be customized through parameterization and also provides restrictions on the basis of users, areas, branches, modules, location, etc. as well as multiple layers of security viz at database level, operating system level, application level and controlled error handling through exceptions.

About the Course

Language of Instruction - English

Course Description

Decorate your house and create attractive gifts and decorative items in Warli art or even start your warli painting business.

The Warlis or Varlis are an indigenous tribe or Adivasis, living in Mountainous as well as coastal areas of Maharashtra - Gujarat border and surrounding areas. Warlis carry on a painting tradition stretching back to 2500 or 3000 BCE. Their extremely rudimentary wall paintings use a very basic graphic vocabulary - a circle, a triangle and a square. Their paintings were monosyllabic.

The circle and triangle come from their observation of nature.
The circle representing the sun and the moon.
The triangle derived from mountains and pointed trees.
Only the square seems to obey a different logic and seems to be a human invention, indicating a sacred enclosure or a piece of land.

In this course, you will learn how to
  1. Draw a human figure in warli painting style
  2. Draw houses in warli painting style
  3. Draw animals and plants in warli painting style
How does this course work?
  1. This course is simple and easy to understand (Will benefit kids and adults and alike).
  2. You will also get full download access to complete master exercise (Useful for painting).
  3. The course comes with ample collection of warli elements and style.
  4. Complete the workbook at your own pace. You can also email your practice drawing and get personal guidance upto 15 days after class.
  5. Use WizIQ discussion board for questions and networking with other students.
The course package
  1. PDFs with chapters
  2. Guidance online on WizIQ or via email - as per your preference

Chapter 1 - Teach how to draw Human figure in warli painting style

  3. Theoretical and practical concepts explained with real life examples
  4. 21+ hours of educational videos
About the Course

Language of Instruction - English

Course Description

The instructor of this course is a highly trained and expert Chartered Accountant. He understands the need to design a course on Financial Management, which stems from the need to demystify the mind-numbing concepts of Finance.

With easy-to-understand concepts, a student gets a grasp on the basics and also understands the real-life implications of the learnt concepts. The course enhances ones ability to analyze various tools of financial planning.

The instructor ensures that upon completion of this course, you get
  1. Management and Financing of Working Capital
  2. Concepts relating to Financing and investment decisions
  3. Fundamentals of Finance to Strategic Finance
  4. Financial Statements effectively for various decision making purposes
The Course is an Ideal for
  1. Aspirants of Exams on Financial Management-CA, ICWA, ACS
  2. MBA & M. Com students
The course coverage ensures high scores on the above mentioned exams. Just to provide you an idea on the weight-age of the topics covered, observe the following
  1. CA (IPCE) - Cost Accounting (50 Marks) and Financial Management (50 Marks)
  2. ICWA (Intermediate Course) - Cost Accounting (60 Marks) and Financial Management (40 Marks)
  3. CS (Professional Programme - Module 2) - Paper 5 - Financial, Treasury and Forex Management.
What you get in the Course
  1. 21+ hours of educational videos
  2. Unlimited online access to the videos for 6 months, giving you the flexibility to watch them at your own time convenience
Note - You are not allowed to download the Videos or share your unique ID

Course Outline

1. Scope and Objectives of Financial Management
2a. Time Value of Money - Theory
2b. Time Value of Money - Practical Problems
3a. Ratio Analysis - Theory
3b. Ratio Analysis - Problems
4. Cash Flow Statements - Theory and Problems
5a. Financing Decisions - Theory
5b. Financing Decisions - Problems
6. Types of Financing - Theory and Problems
7. Investment Decisions - Theory and Problems
8. Management of Working Capital - Theory and Problems
9. Project Finance - Theory and Problems

About the Instructor

CA N. Raja Natarajan - Kochi, India

What makes Mr N. Natarajan, who quit his high paid job to start a CA practice and teach? Passionate! He is Passionate about teaching and that is exactly what prompted him to leave his prosperous career as AVP (Credit) with a leading Public Sector Bank. He is also a practicing Chartered Accountant. Mr Natarajan holds a B. Com from Loyola (Autonomous) College, Chennai and a PGDBM - Finance from Symbiosis Centre for Distance Learning, Pune.

The course and content is his brain child and he has incorporated the real-life scenarios that he encountered on day-to-day basis. These scenarios are covered in the chapters presented in this course.
